{
    "code": "012", 
    "data": "“Say: My lord would not care for you were it not your prayer.”\nOne of the true and authentic feelings of mankind which has an innate root in the nature of man is paying attention to Dua and spiritual relation with the unseen world and the origin of creation.\nThis is a matter which even the famous psychologists have not neglected it. Although the necessity of Dua is present in the nature of man hut it manifests itself more during calamities and misfortunes from materialistic forces. Human being, without any will and option turns himself towards the All-Powerful Allah with all his might and energy; And he asks His help and protection. Dua is the weapon of a Mo’min. It lightens the pressures of misfortunes and difficulties and above all, it showers upon the human being the boundless mercy of the All-Truth (Allah).\nLike other matters, even in the method of Dua, human being is in need of reasonable and rational guidance so that this natural feeling which is necessary for the soul does not mislead him. And it does not become a means and pretext for the cheaters and imposters. With the correct method of its usage, the thirst of the conscience of man gets quenched and finds his intended destination.\nWhen the radiating sun of Islam glittered the Earth and the curtains of superstition were ripped off, its rich resources altered all aspects of individual, social, spiritual, material, and moral affairs of human life. Dua was also amongst the things which were covered by this transformation. Its program is so laid that can be understood as worthy of the affairs of every progressive human being and the true worshipper of Allah.\nIslamic Duas and Ziaraat other than their sacred, holy and divine aspects are the big and comprehensive treasures full of humanistic concepts. Invocating them like attending a training course leaves a very deep and good impression on our personality, the reason being that their interesting meaningful texts are narrated directly from our prophet (s.a.w.a.) and his infallible progeny in which they have taught various lessons about the sublime learning of Monotheism, Resurrection, Prophethood, Wilayat, moral sense, laws and ethics. Indeed, the school of Dua is one of the high schools which is having a great effect in the development of human thinking, spiritual and social growth, of course if it is correctly used. Till the Muslims do not pass this school, their Islamic personality will not become perfect. The school is day and night open for everybody and the repetition of its lessons will always make the person ascend from one stage to another.\nOne of these treasures which, always the believers and those anxious for the reappearance of the righteous and universal Government of Hazrat Baqi-at-Allah (May Allah hasten his Reappearance), have set it as their slogan is the glorious Dua-e-Nudba. They renew their allegiance with their Master during fixed occasions and establish emotional gatherings for reading it.\nNudba (lamentation) and wailing for visiting his Holiness, the coming to an end of his Occultation, pray for hastening his reappearance and expressing regret upon the prevalent turbulent and oppressive condition of today’s world (the Period of Occultation) is a lesson which the Shias have learnt from their Imams (a.s.) and their behaviour is a pattern for their partisans.\nSudair-e-Sairafi, a distinguished companion of Imam Jafar-e-Sadiq (a.s.) says that along with three other companions, they visited Imam (a.s.). They saw Imam (a.s.) in a very sad and sorrowful condition sitting on the ground. Like a mother who has lost her dear son and with a painful heart, Imam (a.s.) was crying, wailing, Moaning and saying:\n“My master, your occultation has snatched away sleep from my eyes, has taken my concentration and has deprived tranquillity from my heart.\nMy master, your occultation has surrounded with a tragic suffering due to which I can never find sympathy and consolation. Due to the loss of friends one after the other, our gathering is breaking.\nCalamities, hardships, difficulties and disasters have so much pained my heart that I do not feel the tears of my eyes and the yelling’s and crying’s of my heart. Yet other severe and unbearable sufferings are imagined that one more difficult and fragile than the previous one.” Sudair says:\nCalamity struck us and our hearts became full of sadness and sorrow for Imam (a.s.). We presumed that an unpleasant event has made Imam (a.s.) – this mountain of patience and forbearance in such a lamenting and mournful condition. We said:\n“O Son of the best mankind, May Allah not make you cry. For what circumstances are you weeping in such a manner His holiness heaved a sad sigh from his afflicted heart and said:\n“This morning, when I was looking at “the book of Jafr”, the book of knowledge of various predicts, until Qiyamat, which has been assigned and made exclusive to Hazrat Mohammad (s.a.w.a.) and his successors (a.s.). It contains the birth, occultation, delay in reappearance, longevity of Hazrat Mahdi (a.t.f.s.), sufferings of believers during occultation, doubts and uncertainties which arise in their hearts due to the prolongation of Occultation , a majority of them leave aside Islam and our wilayat and do not mind about religion. Due to thinking on these things grief and sadness has overpowered me.\nTherefore, with considering the behaviour of Imam (a.s.) regarding the Occultation of Hazrat Mahdi (a.s.), we should also become sad and depressed; and express our wish and interest in his reappearance by seeking shelter .towards Allah and reciting Dua, bearing in mind that if\nHe (Allah) wishes, He can rectify the Occultation of Imam (a.s.) in one night itself.\nDua-e-Nudba is one of the most important and famous authentic Duas of Shia. It’s stability in text, vocabulary and meaningful subjects increase the credibility of its document. This Dua has been narrated by the great Sayyed, the late Razi-ud-Din Ali Ibn-e-Taoos who was from amongst the great Shia scholars of the seventh century. He has narrated in his great books of “Iqbal” pp. 295-299 and the seventh chapter of ‘Misbaah-uz-Zaaer’. Before him, the great sheikh, Mohammad Ibn-e-Jafar-e- Mashadi Haeri who was amongst the great Shia scholars of the sixth century. He has narrated it in his book of ‘Mazaar’ Dua number 107. Prior to these two, Qutb-e- Rawandi who was also amongst the great Shia scholars of the fifth century has written this Dua in his book of ‘Mazaar’. And before all these three persons, the great Shaikh, Mohammad ibn-e-Ali-Ibn-e-Abi Qirra who also was amongst the great Shia scholars of the fifth century has brought it in his book. This book was used by the later scholars. He narrates it from the great and honourable Shaikh, Mohammad Ibn-e-Husain-e-Bazoofari, one of the former learned teacher from whom Shaikh Mufeed was narrating. Bazoofari in his own chain of narrations does not quote its narrators due to its fame and great reputation, he has narrated the Dua from Imam Zaman (a.t.f.s.). He has declared its recitation as a ‘Mustahab Dua’ on four Idds; Jumah, Fitr, Qurban and Ghadeer. Allama Majilisi (May Allah he satisfied with him) also has narrated this Dua in his book of ‘Behaar-ul-Anwaar’ and ‘Zaad-ul-Maad’ from Sayyed Ibn-e-Taoos from the book of Mazaar-e-Mashadi, from Ibn-e-Abu Qirra, from Mohammad Ibn-e-Husain Bazoofari. He testifies to the credibility of its document.\nTherefore, it is necessary that on Friday mornings which is considered as one of the four Idds and the time for the recitation of this great Dua, and during the other mentioned days, in a mass and bewail, with concentrating our mind, asking forgiveness and reciting Salawat, We wash away our sins and remove the obstacles which has stopped the granting of our Duas. Then with a full attention, weeping and moaning state, we call Imam (a.s.) in the same way as Sudair has narrated it from our Sixth Imam, Hazrat Sadiq (a.s.). We cry and recite Nudbah upon the occultation and being far away from Imam (a.s.). We request Allah to hasten his reappearance and thus ends the corruption, persecution and injustice which is reigning in this world due to the absence of Imam (a.s.). May the Almighty Allah has mercy upon our Nudba and moaning. He may have mercy upon a weeping from amongst the weeping’s and will remove the chastisement of Occultation from amongst us. Thus, He may give us the grace and favour of the presence of Imam (a.s.) once more.\nWith His Grace and Benevolence May Allah desire so. \n\nبِسْمِ اللهِ الرَّحْمٰنِ الرَّحِيْمِ \nBISMIL LAAHIR RAHMAANIR RAHEEM\nIn the name of Allah, the Beneficent, the Merciful.\nاَلْحَمْدُ لِلهِ رَبِّ الْعَالَمِيْنَ \nALHAMDO LILLAAHE RABBIL A’ALAMEENA \nPraise be to Allah, the Lord of the Worlds\nوَ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلٰى سَيِّدِنَا مُحَمَّدٍ نَبِيِّهٖ وَ اٰلِهٖ وَ سَلَّمَ تَسْلِيْمًا \nWA SALLAL LAAHO A’LAA SAYYEDENAA MOHAMMADIN NABIYYEHI WA AALEHI WA SALLAMA TASLEEMAN \nAnd Blessings of Allah be upon our master, Mohammad (s.a.w.a.) His Prophet and on his progeny be greetings of Salutation\nاَللّٰهُمَّ لَكَ الْحَمْدُ عَلٰى مَا جَرٰى بِهٖ قَضَآءُكَ فِىْ اَوْلِيَآئِكَ \nALLAAHUMMA LAKAL HAMDO A’LAA MAA JARAA BEHI QAZAAA-OKA FEE AWLEYAAA-EKAL \nO Allah (All) Praise is for you: for all the matters concerning which your Decree was issued regarding your friends\nالَّذِيْنَ اسْتَخْلَصْتَهُمْ لِنَفْسِكَ وَ دِيْنِكَ \nLAZEENAS TAKHLASTAHUM LENAFSEKA WA DEENEKA \nThose whom you have chosen for Yourself and for Your religion\nاِذِ اخْتَرْتَ لَهُمْ جَزِيْلَ مَا عِنْدَكَ مِنَ النَّعِيْمِ الْمُقِيْمِ الَّذِىْ لَا زَوَالَ لَهٗ وَلَا اضْمِحْلَالَ \nEZIKH TARTA LAHUM JAZEELA MAA I’NDAKA MENAN NA-E’EMIL MOQEEMIL LAZEE LAA ZAWAALA LAHU WA LAZ-MEHLAALA \nSince You have decided to bestow on them the choicest of Your everlasting favours, which neither declines nor decreases\nبَعْدَ اَنْ شَرَطْتَ عَلَيْهِمُ الزُّهْدَ فِىْ دَرَجَاتِ هٰذِهِ الدُّنْيَا الدَّنِيَّةِ وَ زُخْرُفِهَا وَ زِبْرِجِهَا \nBA’DA AN SHARATTA A’LAYHEMUZ ZOHDA FEE DARAJAATE HAAZEHID DUNYAD DANIYYATE WA ZUKHROFEHAA WA ZIBREJEHAA \nAfter you took promise from them to renounce all the stages of this despicable world and its superficial attractions and allurements.\nفَشَرَطُوْا لَكَ ذٰلِكَ وَ عَلِمْتَ مِنْهُمُ الْوَفَآءَ بِهٖ\nFA-SHARATOO LAKA ZAALEKA WA ‘ALIMTA MINHOMUL WAFAAA-A BEHI \nThen they accepted the promise and You did know their fulfillment towards it (promise)\nفَقَبِلتَهُمْ وَ قَرَّبْتَهُمْ وَ قَدَّمْتَ لَهُمُ الذِّكْرَ الْعَلِىَّ وَ الثَّنَآءَ الْجَلِىَّ \nFAQABILTAHUM WA QARRABTAHUM WA QADDAMTA LAHOMUZ ZIKRAL A’LIYYA WAS SANAAA-AL JALIYYA \nSo, You accepted them and brought them near to Yourself and accorded for them the exalted remembrance and a glowing praise\nوَ اَهْبَطْتَ عَلَيْهِمْ مَلٰئِكَتَكَ وَ كَرَّمْتَهُمْ بِوَحْيِكَ \nWA AHBATTA A’LAYHIM MALAAA-EKATAKA WA KARRAMTAHUM BE-WAH-YEKA \nAnd You sent down Your angels on them; and honoured them by Your inspirations.\nوَ رَفَدْتَهُمْ بِعِلْمِكَ \nWA RAFADTAHUM BE-I’LMEKA \nAnd helped them with Your knowledge\nوَ جَعَلْتَهُمُ الذَّرِيْعَةَ اِلَيْكَ وَالْوَسِيْلَةَ اِلٰى رِضْوَانِكَ \nWA JA-A’LTAHOMUZ ZAREE-A’TA ELAYKA WAL WASEELATA ELAA RIZWAANEKA \nAnd appointed them as the means of approach to You, and the means towards Your satisfaction.\nفَبَعْضٌ اَسْكَنْتَهٗ جَنَّتَكَ اِلٰى اَنْ اَخْرَجْتَهٗ مِنْهَا \nFA-BA’-ZUN ASKANTAHU JANNATAKA ELAA AN AKHRAJTAHU MINHAA \nThen You made some  of them dwell in Your Garden, until You sent them out there from.\nوَ بَعْضٌ حَمَلْتَهٗ فِىْ فُلْكِكَ وَ نَجَّيْتَهٗ \nWA BA’-ZUN HAMALTAHU FEE FULKEKA WA NAJJAYTAHU \nAnd You carried one of them in Your Ark  and rescued him \nوَ مَنْ اٰمَنَ مَعَهٗ مِنَ الْهَلَكَتِ بِرَحْمَتِكَ \nWA MAN AAMANA MA-A’HU MENAL HALAKATE BERAHMATEKA \nand one who believed with him, by Your Mercy, from destruction.\nوَ بَعْضٌ اِتَّخَذْتَهٗ لِنَفْسِكَ خَلِيْلًا \nWA BA’-ZUN ITTAKHAZTAHU LENAFSEKA KHALEELAN \nAnd you selected for yourself one of them as Your friend.  \nوَ سَئَلَكَ لِسَانَ صِدْقٍ فِى الْاٰخِرِيْنَ فَاَجَبْتَهٗ \nWA SA-ALAKA LESAANA SIDQIN FIL AAKHEREENA FA-AJABTAHU \nAnd he requested you to grant him a tongue of truth in the last epoch of the time. \nوَ جَعَلْتَ ذٰلِكَ عَلِيًّا \nWA JA-A’LTA ZAALEKA A’LIYYAN \nThen You granted his wish and You appointed that elevated one.\nوَ بَعْضٌ كَلَّمْتَهٗ مِنْ شَجَرَةٍ تَكْلِيْمًا \nWA BA’-ZUN KALLAMTAHU MIN SHAJARATIN TAKLEEMAN \nAnd to one of them,  You spoke from a tree a speaking \nوَ جَعَلْتَ لَهٗ مِنْ اَخِيْهِ رِدْئًا وَّ وَزِيْرًا \nWA JA-A’LTA LAHU MIN AKHEEHE RID-AN WA WAZEERAN \nand appointed his brother  his supporter and Vizier\nوَ بَعْضٌ اَوْلَدْتَهٗ مِنْ غَيْرِ اَبٍ وَ اٰتَيْتَهُ الْبَيِّنَاتِ \nWA BA’-ZUN AWLADTAHU MIN GHAYRE ABIN WA AATAYTAHUL BAYYENAATE \nAnd You did cause one  of them to be born without a father and You gave him the clear signs \nوَ اَيَّدْتَهٗ بِرُوْحِ الْقُدُسِ \nWA AYYADTAHU BE-ROOHIL QODOSE \nand supported him with the Holy Spirit.\nوَ كُلٌّ شَرَعْتَ لَهٗ شَرِيْعَةً وَ نَهَجْتَ لَهٗ مِنْهَاجًا \nWA KULLUN SHARA’-TA LAHU SHAREE-A’TAN WA NAHAJTA LAHU MINHAAJAN \nAnd for each one You did enact a religious law and You assigned a path for him\nوَ تَخَيَّرْتَ لَهٗ اَوْصِيَآءَ مُسْتَحْفِظًا بَعْدَ مُسْتَحْفِظٍ \nWA TAKHAYYARTA LAHU AWSEYAAA-A MUSTAHFEZAN BA’-DA MUSTAHFEZIN \nAnd You selected successors  for him A protector after a protector \nمِنْ مُدَّةِ اِلٰى مُدَّةٍ اِقَامَةً لِدِيْنِكَ \nMIN MUDDATIN ELAA MUDDATIN EQAAMATAN LE-DEENEKA \nfor a definite period. For establishing You religion\nوَ حُجَّةً عَلٰى عِبَادِكَ وَ لِئَلَّا يَزُوْلَ الْحَقُّ عَنْ مَقَرِّهٖ \nWA HUJJATAN A’LAA E’BAADEKA WA LE-ALLAA YAZOOLAL HAQQO A’N MAQARREHI \nAnd a proof upon Your servants, lest the truth wanes from its place \nوَ يَغْلِبَ الْبَاطِلُ عَلٰى اَهْلِهٖ \nWA YAGHLEBAL BAATELO A’LAA AHLEHI \nand falsehood overpowers his progeny\nوَ لَا يَقُوْلُ اَحَدٌ لَوْلَا اَرْسَلْتَ اِلَيْنَا رَسُوْلًا مُّنْذِرًا \nWA LAA YAQOOLA AHADUN LAWLAA ARSALTA ELAYNAA RASOOLAN MUNZERAN \nAnd none can say: Why had You not sent unto us a warning messenger  \nوَ اَقَمْتَ لَنَا عَلَمًا هَادِيًا \nWA AQAMTA LANAA A’LAMAN HAADEYAN \nand appointed for us a flag of guidance. \nفَنَتَّبِعَ اٰيَاتِكَ مِنْ قَبْلِ اَنْ نَذِلَّ وَ نَخْزٰى \nFANATTABE-A’ AAYAATEKA MIN QABLE AN NAZILLA WA NAKHZAA \nThen we would have followed Your signs before suffering failure and disgrace\nاِلٰى اَنِ انْتَهَيْتَ بِالْاَمْرِ اِلٰى حَبِيْبِكَ وَ نَجِيْبِكَ \nELAA ANIN TAHAYTA BIL-AMRE ELAA HABEEBEKA WA NAJEEBEKA \nTill You ended the affair  towards Your beloved and Your noble \nمُحَمَّدٍ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَ اٰلِهٖ \nMOHAMMADIN SALLAL LAAHO A’LAYHE WA AALEHI \nMohammad, May the peace of Allah be upon him and his progeny\nفَكَانَ كَمَا انْتَجَبْتَهٗ سَيِّدَ مَنْ خَلَقْتَهٗ \nFA-KAANA KAMAN TAJABTAHU SAYYEDA MAN KHALAQTAHU \nThen, he was as You had selected him, the leader of whom You have created him \nوَ صَفْوَةَ مِنَ اصْطَفَيْتَهٗ \nWA SAFWATA MANIS- TAFAYTAHU \nand the excellent one of Your selected one; \nوَ اَفْضَلَ مَنِ اجْتَبَيْتَهٗ \nWA AFZALA MANIJ TABAYTAHU \nand the best one whom You have selected him \nوَ اَكْرَمَ مَنِ اعْتَمَدْتَهٗ \nWA AKRAMA MANEA’ TAMADTAHU \nand the most honoured whom You have relied on him\nقَدَّمْتَهٗ عَلٰى اَنْبِيَآئِكَ وَ بَعَثْتَهٗ اِلٰى الثَّقَلَيْنِ مِنْ عِبَادِكَ \nQADDAMTAHU A’LAA AMBEYAAA-EKA WA BA-A’STAHU ELAS-SAQALAYNE MIN E’BAADEKA \nYou gave him precedence upon Your prophets and have sent him to the thaqalain  (Jinns and Men) from (among) Your servants. \nوَ اَوْطَاْتَهٗ مَشَارِقَكَ وَ مَغَارِبَكَ \nWA AW-TAATAHU MASHAAREQAKA WA MAGHAAREBAKA \nAnd made Your Easts and Wests  come under his feet; \nوَ سَخَّرْتَ لَهُ الْبُرَاقَ \nWA SAKHKHARTA LAHUL BORAAQA \nand harnessed for him the Buraq.  \nوَ عَرَجْتَ بِرُوْحِهٖ اِلٰى سَمَآئِكَ \nWA A’RAJTA BE ROOHE-HI ELAA SAMAAA-EKA \nAnd did make him ascend (with his soul) towards Your heavens\nوَ اَوْدَعْتَهٗ عِلْمَ مَا كَانَ وَ مَا يَكُوْنُ اِلَى انْقِضَآءِ خَلْقِكَ \nWA AWDA’-TAHU I’LMA MAA KAANA WA MAA YAKOONO ELAN QEZAAA-E KHALQEKA \nAnd You entrusted in him the knowledge of the past and future till the end of Your creation\nثُمَّ نَصَرْتَهُ بِالرُّعْبِ \nSUMMA NASARTAHU BIR ROA’-BE \nThen You helped him with awe \nوَ حَفَفْتَهٗ بِجَبْرَئِيْلَ وَ مِيْكَائِيْلَ \nWA HAFAFTAHU BE-JABRA-EELA WA MEEKAA-EELA \nand You surrounded him with Jibraeel and Michaeel \nوَالْمُسَوِّمِيْنَ مِنْ مَّلٰئِكَتِكَ \nWAL MOSAWWEMEENA MIN MALAAA-EKATEKA \nand the distinguished angels. \nوَ وَعَدْتَهٗ اَنْ تُظْهِرَ دِيْنَهٗ عَلَى الدِّيْنِ كُلِّهٖ \nWA WA-AZTAHU AN TUZHERA DEENAHU A’LAD DEENE KULLEHI \nAnd You promised him that You would make his religion triumphant over all the religions \nوَ لَوْكَرِهَ الْمُشْرِكُوْنَ \nWA LAW-KAREHAL MUSHREKOONA \nthough the polytheists may be averse  (to it)\nوَ ذٰلِكَ بَعْدَ اَنْ بَوَّئْتَهٗ مُبَوَّ ءَصِدْقٍ مِنْ اَهْلِهٖ \nWA ZAALEKA BA’-DA AN BAWWA-TAHU MOBAWWA-A SIDQIN MIN AHLEHI \nAnd this is after You appointed some of his kindered as his Successor\nوَ جَعَلْتَ لَهٗ وَ لَهُمْ اَوَّلَ بَيْتٍ وُّضِعَ لِلنَّاسِ \nWA JA-A’LTA LAHU WA LAHUM AWWALA BAYTIN WOZE-A’ LIN-NAASE \nAnd You appointed for him and them a First house which has been established for the mankind. \nلَلَّذِىْ بِبَكَّةَ مُبَارَكًا وَّ هُدًى لِّلْعَالَمِيْنَ \nLAL-LAZEE BE-BAKKATA MOBAARAKAN WA HODAL LIL A’ALAMEENA \nThe one which is at Makkah, a blessing and a guidance for the worlds\nفِيْهِ اٰيَاتٌ بَيِّنَاتٌ مَّقَامُ اِبْرَاهِيْمَ وَ مَنْ دَخَلَهٗ كَانَ اٰمِنًا \nFEEHE AAYAATUN BAYYENAATUN MAQAAMO IBRAAHEEMA WA MAN DAKHALAHU KAANA AAMENAN \nIn it (are) clear sings; place of Ibrahim and whoever entered it in was safe. \nوَ قُلْتَ اِنَّمَا يُرِيْدُ اللهُ لِيُذْهِبَ عَنْكُمُ الرِّجْسَ اَهْلَ الْبَيْتِ وَ يُطَهِّرَكُمْ تَطْهِيْرًا \nWA QULTA INNAMAA YOREEDUL LAAHO LE-YUZHEBA A’NKOMUR RIJSA AHLAL BAYTE WA YOTAHHERAKUM TATHEERAA \nAnd You said: Verily Allah intends to keep off from you every kind of uncleanliness. And to purify you people of the House with a thorough purification. \nثُمَّ جَعَلْتَ اَجْرَ مُحَمَّدٍ صَلَوَاتُكَ عَلَيْهِ وَ اٰلِهٖ \nSUMMA JA-A’LTA AJRA MOHAMMADIN SALAWAATOKA A’LAYHE WA AALEHI\nThen You assigned rewards of Mohammad, Your peace be upon him and his progeny (with) \nمَوَدَّتَهُمْ فِىْ كِتَابِكَ فَقُلْتَ \nMAWADDATAHUM FEE KETAABEKA FA-QULTA \ntheir love (the love of progeny) in Your Book. Then You said:\nقُلْ لَّا اَسْئَلُكُمْ عَلَيْهِ اَجْرًا اِلَّا الْمَوَدَّةَ فِى الْقُرْبٰى \nQUL LAA AS-ALOKUM A’LAYHE AJRAN ILLAL MAWADDATA FIL QURBAA \n “Say I demand not, of you any reward for it” (the toils of preaching except the love of my relations. \nوَ قُلْتَ مَا سَئَلْتُكُمْ مِنْ اَجْرٍ فَهُوَ لَكُمْ \nWA QULTA MAA SA-ALTOKUM MIN AJRIN FAHOWA LAKUM \nAnd you said: “Whatever reward I have asked you  it is for yourself.”\nوَ قُلْتَ مَا اَسْئَلُكُمْ عَلَيْهِ مِنْ اَجْرٍ اِلَّا مَنْ شَآءَ \nWA QULTA MAA AS-ALOKUM A’LAYHE MIN AJRIN ILLAA MAN SHAAA-A \nAnd you said: “I ask you not any reward for it except that one who wishes, \nاَنْ يَّتَّخِذَ اِلٰى رَبِّهِ سَبِيْلًا \nANY YATTAKHEZA ELAA RABBEHI SABEELAN \nmay adopt the path of His Lord. \nفَكَانُوْا هُمُ السَّبِيْلَ اِلَيْكَ وَ الْمَسْلَكَ اِلٰى رِضْوَانِكَ \nFA-KAANOO HOMUS SABEELA ELAYKA WAL MASLAKA ELAA RIZWAANEKA \nThen, they [Ahlul Bait (a.s.)] are the path towards You and the way towards Your satisfaction.\nفَلَمَّا انْقَضَتْ اَيَّامُهٗ \nFALAMMAN QAZAT AYYAAMOHU \nWhen his (Holy Prophet) days passed.\nاَقَامَ وَلِيَّهِ عَلِىَّ بْنَ اَبِىْ طَالِبٍ صَلَوٰتُكَ عَلَيْهِمَا وَ اٰلِهِمَا هَادِيًا \nAQAAMA WALIYYAHU A’LIYYABNA ABEE TAALEBIN SALAWAATOKA A’LAYHEMAA WA AALEHEMAA HAADEYAN \nBe appointed his successor Ali, son of Abu Talib as a Guide. Your peace be upon them and their progeny. \nاِذْ كَانَ هُوَ الْمُنْذِرَ وَ لِكُلِّ قَوْمٍ هَادٍ \nIZ KAANA HOWAL MUNZERA WA LE-KULLE QAWMIN HAADIN \nAs he was a warner – and a Guide for every nation. \nفَقَالَ وَالْمَلَاءُ اَمَامَهٗ \nFA-QAALA WAL MALA-O AMAAMAHU \nThen he (Holy Prophet) said before a huge gathering\nمَنْ كُنْتُ مَوْلَاهُ فَعَلِىٌّ مَوْلَاهُ \nMAN KUNTO MAWLAAHO FA-A’LIYYUN MAWLAAHO \n “Whomsoever I am his Master, then Ali, is his Master\nاَللّٰهُمَّ وَ آلِ مَنْ وَالَاهُ وَ عَادِ مَنْ عَادَاهُ \nALLAAHUMMA WAALE MAN WAALAAHO WA A’ADE MAN A’ADAAHO \nO Allah Be a friend of one who is his friend and be the enemy of one who is his enemy; \nوَانْصُرْ مَنْ نَصَرَهٗ وَاخْذُلْ مَنْ خَذَلَهٗ \nWAN-SUR MAN NASARAHU WAKH-ZUL MAN KHAZALAHU \nand help one who helps him and disgrace one who disgraces him” \nوَ قَالَ مَنْ كُنْتُ اَنَا نَبِيَّهٗ فَعَلِىٌّ اَمِيْرُهٗ \nWA QAALA MAN KUNTO ANAA NABIYYAHU FA-A’LIYYUN AMEEROHU \nAnd he said: “Of whomsoever I am his Prophet, then Ali is his Chief” \nوَ قَالَ اَنَا وَ عَلِىٌّ مِّنْ شَجَرَةٍ وَاْحِدَةٍ \nWA QAALA ANAA WA A’LYYUN MIN SHAJARATIN WAAHEDATIN \nوَ سَائِرُ النَّاسِ مِنْ شَجَرَةٍ شَتّٰى \nWA SAA-IRUN NAASO MIN SHAJARIN SHATTAA \nand the other people are from different trees.” \nوَ اَحَلَّهٗ مَحَلَّ هَارُوْنَ مِنْ مُوْسٰى فَقَالَ لَهٗ \nWA AHALLAHU MAHALLA HAAROONA MIN MOOSAA FA QAALA LAHU \nAnd he placed him [Ali (a.s.)] in a position, as Haroon had with Moosa. Then he said to him,\nاَنْتَ مِنِّىْ بِمَنْزِلَةِ هَارُوْنَ مِنْ مُوْسٰى اِلَّا اَنَّهٗ لَا نَبِىَّ بَعْدِىْ \nANTA MINNEE BE-MANZELATE HAAROONA MIN MOOSAA ILLAA ANNAHU LAA NABIYYA BA’-DEE \n“your position to me is as Haroon had with Moosa, except that there will be no Prophet after me.” \nوَ زَوَّجَهُ ابْنَتَهٗ سَيِّدَةَ نِسَآءِ الْعَالَمِيْنَ \nWA ZAWWAJAHUB-NATAHU SAYYEDATA NESAAA-IL A’ALAMEENA \nAnd he got him married with his daughter, chief of the ladies of the Worlds. \nوَ اَحَلَّ لَهٗ مِنْ مَسْجِدِهٖ مَا حَلَّ لَهٗ \nWA AHALLA LAHU MIN MASJEDEHI MAA HALLA LAHU \nAnd he made for him lawful [Ali (a.s.)] whatever was lawful for himself in his mosque.\nوَ سَدَّ الْاَبْوَابَ اِلَّا بَابَهٗ \nWA SADDAL ABWAABA ILLAA BAABAHU \nAnd he closed all the doors (leading to the mosque) except the door of his house. \nثُمَّ اَوْدَعَهٗ عِلْمَهٗ وَ حِكْمَتَهِ فَقَالَ:\nSUMMA AWDA-A’HU I’LMAHU WA HIKMATAHU FA-QAALA:\nThen he (Holy Prophet) entrusted to him his knowledge and his wisdom. Then he said,\nاَنَا مَدِيْنَةُ الْعِلْمِ وَ عَلِىٌّ بَابُهَا \nANAA MADEENATUL I’LME WA A’LIYYUN BAABOHAA \n“I am the city of knowledge and Ali is its gate. \nفَمَنْ اَرَادَ الْمَدِيْنَةَ وَ الْحِكْمَةَ فَلْيَاْتِهَا مِنْ بَابِهَا \nFAMAN ARAADAL MADEENATA WAL HIKMATA FALYAATEHAA MIN BAABEHAA \nThen, one who wishes (to enter) the city (of knowledge) and wisdom, then he should enter from its gate.” \nثُمَّ قَالَ اَنْتَ اَخِىْ وَ وَصِيِّىْ وَ وَارِثِىْ \nSUMMA QAALA ANTA AKHEE WA WASIYYEE WA WAARESEE \nThen, he said, “you are my brother and successor and inheritor.”\nلَحْمُكَ مِنْ لَحْمِىْ وَ دَمُكَ مِنْ دَمِىْ \nLAHMOKA MIN LAHMEE WA DAMOKA MIN DAMEE \nYour flesh is from my flesh And your blood from my blood\nوَ سِلْمُكَ سِلْمِىْ وَ حَرْبُكَ حَرْبِىْ \nWA SILMOKA SILMEE WA HARBOKA HARBEE \nAnd peace with you is peace with me and fight with you is fight with me.\nوَ الْاِيْمَانُ مُخَالِطٌ لَحْمَكَ وَ دَمَكَ كَمَا خَالَطَ لَحْمِىْ وَدَمِىْ \nWAL EEMAANO MOKHAALETUN LAHMAKA WA DAMAKA KAMAA KHAALATA LAHMEE WA DAMEE \nAnd the faith is mixed with your flesh and your blood as it is mixed with my flesh and my blood\nوَ اَنْتَ غَدًا عَلَى الْحَوْضِ خَلِيْفَتِىْ \nWA ANTA GHADAN A’LAL HAWZE KHALEEFATEE \nAnd tomorrow, you will be my successor at the Cistern Kausar Pond (Hawz of Kausar)\nوَ اَنْتَ تَقْضِىْ دَيْنِىْ وَ تُنْجِزُ عِدَاتِىْ \nWA ANTA TAQZEE DAYNEE WA TUNJEZO E’DAATEE \nAnd you will repay my debt and you will fulfill my promises\nوَ شِيْعَتُكَ عَلٰى مَنَابِرَ مِنْ نُوْرٍ \nWA SHEE-A’TOKA A’LAA MANAABERA MIN NOORIN \nAnd your shias (followers) will be (sitting) on the pulpits of light; \nمُبْيَضَّةً وُجُوْهُهُمْ حَوْلِىْ فِى الْجَنَّةِ وَ هُمْ جِيْرَانِىْ \nMUBYAZZATAN WOJOOHOHUM HAWLEE FIL JANNATE WA HUM JEERAANEE \nwith bright faces surrounding me in the Heaven and they will be my neighbours. \nوَ لَوْلَا اَنْتَ يَا عَلِىُّ لَمْ يُعْرَفِ الْمُؤْمِنُوْنَ بَعْدِىْ \nWA LAW-LAA ANTA YAA A’LIYYO LAM YOA’-RAFIL MO-MINOONA BA’-DEE \nAnd (he said), “O Ali, had you not been there, the believer would not have been recognized after me” \nوَ كَانَ بَعْدَهٗ هُدًى مِّنَ الضَّلَالِ وَ نُوْرًا مِّنَ الْعَمٰى \nWA KAANA BA’-DAHU HODAN MENAZ ZALAALE WA NOORAN MENAL A’MAA \nAnd he was a guidance (to prevent people) from deviation after him (the Holy Prophet) and a light from the blindness\nوَ حَبْلَ اللهِ الْمَتِيْنَ وَ صِرَاطَهُ الْمُسْتَقِيْمَ \nWA HABLALLAAHIL MATEENA WA SERAATAHUL MUSTAQEEMA \nAnd the strong rope of Allah and His Right Path. \nوَلَا يُسْبَقُ بِقَرَابَةٍ فِىْ رَحِمٍ \nLAA YUSBAQO BEQARAABATIN FEE RAHEMIN \nNeither his Proximity in the ties of relationship (with the Holy Prophet) can be preceded (by anyone)\nوَ لَا بِسَابِقَةٍ فِىْ دِيْنٍ \nWA LAA BE-SAABEQATIN FEE DEENIN \nNor his preceding in religion\nوَ لَا يُلْحَقُ فِىْ مَنْقَبَةٍ مِنْ مَنَاقِبِهٖ \nWA LAA YULHAQO FEE MANQABATIN MIN MANAAQEBEHI \nAnd (no one) can overtake any virtues from amongst his (prophet) virtues. \nيَحْذُوْ حَذْوَ الرَّسُوْلِ \nYAHZOO HAZWAR RASOOLE \nHe (Ali) follows the path of the Messenger \nصَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِمَا وَ اٰلِهِمَا \nSALLALLAAHU A’LAYHEMAA WA AALEHEMAA \nMay the blessings of Allah be upon both of them and their progeny.\nوَ يُقَاتِلُ عَلَى التَّاْوِيْلِ \nWA YOQAATELO A’LAT TAAWEELE \nAnd he fights on (the basis of) interpretation \nوَ لَا تَاخُذُهٗ فِى اللهِ لَوْمَتُ لَآئِمٍ \nWA LAA TAA-KHOZOHU FILLAAHE LAWMATO LAAA-EMIN \nAnd he cares not for any blame of any rebuker in the way of Allah\nقَدْ وَتَرَ فِيْهِ صَنَادِيْدَ الْعَرَبِ \nQAD WATARA FEEHE SANAADEEDAL A’RABE \nand killed their valiant fighters and attacked their wolves.\nوَ قَتَلَ اَبْطَالَهُمْ وَ نَاوَشَ ذُؤْبَانَهُمْ \nWA QATALA ABTAALAHUM WA NAAWASHA ZOA-BAANAHUM \nIndeed, he has spilled the blood of the heroes of Arabia, \nفَاَوْدَعَ قُلُوْبَهُمْ اَحْقَادًا بَدْرِيَّةً وَّ خَيْبَرِيَّةً وَّ حُنَيْنِيَّةً وَ غَيْرَ هُنَّ \nFA-AWDA-A’ QOLOOBAHUM AHQAADAN BADRIYYATAN WA KHAYBARIYYATAN WA HONAYNIYYATAN WA GHAYRA HUNNA \nThen he filled the hearts of them (fighters) of Badr, Khaibar, Hunain and of others  with a hatred and malice.\nفَاَضَبَّتْ عَلٰى عَدَاوَتِهٖ وَ اَكَبَّتْ عَلٰى مُنَابَذَتِهٖ \nFA-AZABBAT A’LAA A’DAAWATEHI WA AKABBAT A’LAA MONAABAZATEHI \nThen, (they) rose in enmity, against him, and (they) attacked to fight against him.\nحَتّٰى قَتَلَ النَّاكِثِيْنَ وَ الْقَاسِطِيْنَ وَ الْمَارِقِيْنَ \nHATTAA QATALAN NAAKESEENA WAL QAASETEENA WAL MAAREQEENA \nTill (such time) that he killed the oath breakers of allegiance,  the unjust,  and the (Maareqeen) Renegades. \nوَ لَمَّا قَضٰى نَحْبَهٗ وَ قَتَلَهٗ اَشْقَى الْاٰخِرِيْنَ يَتْبَعُ اَشْقَى الْاَوَّلِيْنَ \nWA LAMMAA QAZAA NAHBAHU WA QATALAHU ASHQAL AAKHEREENA YATBA-O’ ASHQAL AWWALEENA \nAnd when his term of life expired, a wretched person among those of the last epoch, following the path of those of the earlier period killed him. \nلَمْ يُمْتَثَلْ اَمْرُ رَسُوْلِ اللهِ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَ اٰلِهٖ \nLAM YUMTASAL AMRO RASOOLILLAAHE SALLAL LAAHO A’LAYHE WA AALEHI \n(the) order of the Messenger of Allah, peace of Allah be upon him and his Progeny, \nفِى الْهَادِيْنَ بَعْدَ الْهَادِيْنَ \nFIL HAADEENA \nwas not obeyed about the leaders (Imams) one after the other.\nوَ الْاُمَّةُ مُصِرَّةٌ عَلٰى مَقْتِهٖ مُجْتَمِعَةٌ عَلٰى قَطِيْعَةِ رَحِمِهٖ \nBA’-DAL HAADEENA WAL UMMATO MOSIRRATUN A’LAA MAQTEHI MUJTAME-A’TUN A’LAA QATEE-A’TE RAHEMEHI \nAnd the Ummah was insistent on bearing enmity against him. They joined together to cut off his ties of relations (Holy Prophet) \nوَاِقْصَآءِ وُلْدِهٖ \nWA IQSAA-E WULDEHI\nand throwing away his children (from successorship).\nاِلَّا الْقَلِيْلَ مِمَّنْ وَفٰى لِرِعَايَةِ الْحَقِّ فِيْهِمْ \nILLAL QALEELA MIMMAN WAFAA LE-RE-A’A-YATIL HAQQE FEEHIM \nExcept a few from then (believers) who remained faithful in observing their (Ahl-e-Bait’s) rights\nفَقُتِلَ مَنْ قُتِلَ \nFA-QOTELA MAN QOTELA \nThen some of them were killed \nوَ سُبِىَ مَنْ سُبِىَ \nWA SOBEYA MAN SOBEYA \nAnd some were taken into captivity \nوَ اُقْصِىَ مَنْ اُقْصِىَ \nWA UQSEYA MAN UQSEYA \nAnd some were exiled. \nوَ جَرَى الْقَضَآءُ لَهُمْ بِمَا يُرْجٰى لَهٗ حُسْنُ الْمَثُوْبَةِ\nWA JARAL QAZAAA-O LAHUM BEMAA YURJAA LAHU HUSNUL MASOOBATE \nAnd the decree was to pass from them, with this hope that the best reward is in it.\nاِذْ كَانَتِ الْاَرْضُ لِلّٰهِ يُوْرِثُهَا مَنْ يَشَآءُ مِنْ عِبَادِهٖ \nIZ KAANATIL ARZO LILLAAHE YOORESOHAA MAN YASHAAA-O MIN E’BAADEHI \nSince the Earth belongs to Allah. He gives to whomsoever He wishes from amongst His servants. \nوَ الْعَاقِبَةُ لِلْمُتَّقِيْنَ \nWAL A’AQEBATO LIL-MUTTAQEENA \nAnd the end is (only) for those who guard against evil. \nوَ سُبْحَانَ رَبِّنَا اِنْ كَانَ وَعْدُ رَبِّنَا لَمَفْعُوْلًا \nWA SUBHAANA RABBENAA IN KAANA WA’DO RABBENAA LA MAFOOLAN \nAnd glorious in our Lord, Verily the promise of our Lord is certainly to be fulfilled.  \nوَ لَنْ يُّخْلِفَ اللهُ وَعْدَهٗ وَ هُوَ الْعَزِيْزُ الْحَكِيْمُ \nWA LANY YUKHLEFAL LAAHO WA’-DAHU WA HOWAL A’ZEEZUL HAKEEMO \nAnd Allah never goes against His promise; and He is the All-Mighty, All-Wise. \nفَعَلَى الْاَطَائِبِ مِنْ اَهْلِ بَيْتِ مُحَمَّدٍ وَ عَلِىٍّ  \nFA-A’LAL ATAA-EBE MIN AHLE BAYTE MOHAMMADIN WA A’LIYYIN \nThe upon the purified ones of the purified ones of the progeny of Mohammad and Ali \nصَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِمَا وَ اٰلِهِمَا فَلْيَبْكِ الْبَاكُوْنَ \nSALLAL LAAHO A’LAYHEMAA WA AALEHEMAA FAL-YABKIL BAAKOONA \nMay the peace of Allah be upon both of them and their progeny. The believers should cry.\nوَ اِيَّاهُمْ فَلْيَنْدُبِ النَّادِبُوْنَ \nWA IYYAAHUM FAL-YANDOBIN NAADEBOONA \nAnd the wailers should wail upon them.\nوَ لِمِثْلِهِمْ فَلْتُذْرَفِ الدُّمُوْعُ \nWA LE-MISLEHIM FAL-TUZ-RAFID DOMOO-O’ \nAnd for such people like them, then the tears should flow\nوَ الْيَصْرُخِ الصَّارِخُوْنَ \nWAL YASROKHIS SAAREKHOONA \nAnd the clamourers should clamour \nوَ يَضِجَّ الضَّآجُّوْنَ وَ يَعِجُّ الْعَآجُّوْنَ \nWA YAZIJJAZ ZAAAJJOONA WA YA-I’JJAL A’AAJJOONA \nand the mourners should mourn in a heart rending manner:\nاَيْنَ الْحَسَنُ اَيْنَ الْحُسَيْنُ اَيْنَ اَبْنَآءُ الْحُسَيْنِ؟\nAYNAL HASANO AYNAL HUSAYNO AYNA ABNAAA-UL HUSAYNE \nWhere is Hasan? Where is Husain? Where are the children of Husain?\nصَالِحٌ بَعْدَ صَالِحٍ وَ صَادِقٌ بَعْدَ صَادِقٍ \nSAALEHUN BA’-DA SAALEHIN WA SAADEQUN BA’-DA SAADEQIN \nThe Righteous after righteous and truthful after truthful.\nاَيْنَ السَّبِيْلُ بَعْدَ السَّبِيْلِ؟\nAYNAS SABEELO BA’-DAS SABEELE \nWhere is the path after the path (of righteousness)?\nاَيْنَ الْخِيَرَةُ بَعْدَ الْخِيَرَةِ ؟\nAYNAL KHEYARATO BA’-DAL KHEYARATE \nWhere are the virtuous people after the virtuous ones?\nاَيْنَ الشُّمُوْسُ الطَّالِعَةُ ؟\nAYNASH SHOMOOSUT TAALE-A’TO \nWhere are the rising suns?\nاَيْنَ الْاَقْمَارُ الْمُنِيْرَةُ؟\nAYNAL AQMAARUL MONEERATO \nWhere are the luminous Moons?\nاَيْنَ الْاَنْجُمُ الظَّاهِرَةُ؟\nAYNAL ANJOMUZ ZAAHERATO \nWhere are the brilliant stars?\nاَيْنَ اَعْلَامُ الدِّيْنِ وَ قَوَاعِدُ الْعِلْمِ؟\nAYNA AA’-LAAMUD DEENE WA QAWAA-E’DUL I’LME \nWhere are the Emblems of the Faith and the Basis of knowledge?\nاَيْنَ بَقِيَّةُ اللهِ الَّتِىْ لَا تَخْلُوْ مِنَ الْعِتْرَةِ الْهَادِيَةِ ؟\nAYNA BAQIYYATULLAAHIL LATEE LAA TAKHLOO MENAL I’TRATIL HAADEYATE \nWhere is the Baqi-at-Allah?  Which (the world) cannot be devoid from (the presence of) guided progeny? \nاَيْنَ الْمُعَدُّ لِقَطْعِ دَابِرِ الظَّلَمَةِ ؟\nAYNAL MO-A’DDO LE-QAT-E’ DAABERIZ ZALAMATE \nWhere is the one ready to annihilate the oppressors? \nاَيْنَ الْمُنْتَظَرُ لِاِقَامَةِ الْاَمْتِ وَ الْعِوَجَ؟\nAYNAL MUNTAZARO LE-EQAAMATIL AMTE WAL E’WAJE \nWhere is the Awaited one for straightening the crookedness and dishonesty?\nاَيْنَ الْمُرْتَجٰى لِاِزَالَةِ الْجَوْرِ وَ الْعُدْوَانِ؟\nAYNAL MURTAJAA LE-EZAALATIL JAWRE WAL U’DWAANE \nWhere is the Expected (Imam Mahdi) for abolishing the oppression and transgression?\nاَيْنَ الْمُدَّخَرُ لِتَجْدِيْدِ الْفَرَائِضِ وَالسُّنَنِ؟\nAYNAL MUDDAKHARO LE-TAJDEEDIL FARAA-EZE WAS SONANE \nWhere is the one stored for reviving the obligatory command and the Sunnah (of the Holy Prophet)?\nاَيْنَ الْمُتَخَيَّرُ لِاِعَادَةِ الْمِلَّةِ وَ الشَّرِيْعَةِ ؟\nAYNAL MOTAKHAYYARO LE-E-A’ADATIL MILLATE WASH SHAREE-A’T \nWhere is the selected one for resuscitating (the reality) of the nation and the religion?\nاَيْنَ الْمُؤَمَّلُ لِاِحْيَآءِ الْكِتَابِ وَ حُدُوْدِهٖ؟\nAYNAL MO-AMMALO LE-EHYAAA-IL KETAABE WA HODOODEHI \nWhere is the expected one for enlivening the Book and its limits?\nاَيْنَ مُحْيِىْ مَعَالِمِ الدِّيْنِ وَ اَهْلِهٖ؟\nAYNA MOHYEE MA-A’ALEMID DEENE WA AHLEHI \nWhere is the Enlivener of the precepts of religion and its adherents?\nاَيْنَ قَاصِمُ شَوْكَةِ الْمُعْتَدِيْنَ؟\nAYNA QAASEMO SHAWKATIL MOA’-TADEENA \nWhere is the breaker of the might of the transgressors?\nاَيْنَ هَادِمُ اَبْنِيَّةِ الشِّرْكِ وَ النِّفَاقِ؟\nAYNA HAADEMO ABNIYYATISH SHIRKE WAN NEFAAQE \nWhere is the demolisher of the edifices of polytheism and hypocrisy?\nاَيْنَ مُبِيْدُ اَهْلِ الْفُسُوْقِ وَ الْعِصْيَانِ وَ الطُّغْيَانِ؟\nAYNA MOBEDO AHLIL FOSOOQE WAL I’SYAANE WAT TUGH-YAANE \nWhere is the destroyer of the followers of transgression, disobedience and rebellion?\nاَيْنَ حَاصِدُ فُرُوْعِ الْغَىِّ وَ الشِّقَاقِ؟\nAYNA HAASEDO FUROO-I’L GHAYYE WASH SHEQAAQE \nWhere is the Eradicator of branches of errors and disputes?\nاَيْنَ طَامِسُ اٰثَارِ الزَّيْغِ وَ الْاَهْوَآءِ؟\nAYNA TAAMESO AASAARIZ ZAYGHE WAL AHWAAA-E \nWhere is the Destroyer of the signs of (evil) disease and egoistic tendencies?\nاَيْنَ قَاطِعُ حَبَآئِلِ الْكِذْبِ وَ الْاِفْتِرَاءِ؟\nAYNA QAATE-O’ HABAAA ELIL KIZBE WAL IFTERAAA-E \nWhere is the severer of the cords of falsehood and calumniation?\nاَيْنَ مُبِيْدُ الْعُتَاةِ وَ الْمَرَدَةِ؟\nAYNA MOBEEDUL O’TAATE WAL MARADATE \nWhere is the Destroyer of the vicious and disobedient people?\nاَيْنَ مُسْتَاْصِلُ اَهْلِ الْعِنَادِ وَ التَّضْلِيْلِ وَالْاِلْحَادِ؟\nAYNA MUSTAA-SELU AHLIL E’NAADE WAT TAZLEELE WAL ILHAADE \nWhere is the Eradicator of the followers of obstinacy and misguidance and the renegade?\nاَيْنَ مُعِزُّ الْاَوْلِيَآءِ وَ مُذِلُّ الْاَعْدَاءِ؟\nAYNA MO-I’ZZUL AWLEYAAA-E WA MOZILLUL AA’-DAA-E \nWhere is the one who honours the friends and Debases the enemy?\nاَيْنَ جَامِعُ الْكَلِمَةِ عَلَى التَّقْوٰى؟\nAYNA JAAME-U’L KALEMATE A’LAT TAQWAA \nWhere is the Accumulator of the words of piety?\nاَيْنَ بَابُ اللهِ الَّذِىْ مِنْهُ يُؤْتٰى؟\nAYNA BAABUL LAAHIL LAZEE MINHO YOATAA \nWhere is the Gate of Allah through which all should enter? \nاَيْنَ وَجْهُ اللهِ الَّذِىْ اِلَيْهِ يَتَوَجَّهُ الْاَوْلِيَآءُ؟\nAYNA WAJHUL LAAHIL LAZEE ELAYHE YATAWAJJAHUL AWLEYAAA-O \nWhere is the Countenance of Allah through which the friends attend towards him?\nاَيْنَ السَّبَبُ الْمُتَّصِلُ بَيْنَ الْاَرْضِ وَ السَّمَآءِ؟\nAYNAS SABABUL MUTASSELO BAYNAL ARZE WAS SAMAAA-E \nWhere is the Means which is stretching from the Earth to the sky?\nاَيْنَ صَاحِبُ يَوْمِ الْفَتْحِ وَ نَاشِرُ رَايَةِ الْهُدٰى؟\nAYNA SAAHEBO YAWMIL FATHE WA NAASHERO RAAYATIL HODAA \nWhere is the Master of the Day of Victory and the one who will spread the flag of Guidance?\nاَيْنَ مُؤَلِّفُ شَمْلِ الصَّلَاحِ وَ الرِّضَا؟\nAYNA MO-ALLEFO SHAMLIS SALAAHE WAR REZAA \nWhere is the uniter of the companions of virtue and divine pleasure?\nاَيْنَ الطَّالِبُ بِذُحُوْلِ الْاَنْبِيَآءِ وَ اَبْنَآءِ الْاَنْبِيَآءِ؟\nAYNAT TAALEBO BE-ZOHOOLIL AMBEYAAA-E WA ABNAAA-IL AMBEYAAA-E \nWhere is the Avenger of the blood of prophets and the children of the prophets? \nاَيْنَ الطَّالِبُ بِدَمِ الْمَقْتُوْلِ بِكَرْبَلَاءَ؟\nAYNAT TAALEBO BE-DAMIL MAQTOOLE BE-KARBALAA-A \nWhere is the seeker of revenge for the blood of the Martyred ones of Karbala? \nاَيْنَ الْمَنْصُوْرُ عَلٰى مَنِ اعْتَدٰى عَلَيْهِ وَافْتَرٰى؟\nAYNAL MANSOORO A’LAA MANEA’-TADAA A’LAYHE WAF-TARAA \nWhere is the Truimphant one (who will overcome) over one who transgressed against him and maligned him?\nاَيْنَ الْمُضْطَرُّ الَّذِىْ يُجَابُ اِذَا دَعَا؟\nAYNAL MUZTARRUL LAZEE YOJAABO EZAA DA-A’A \nWhere is the distressed one who will be answered when he supplicates?\nاَيْنَ صَدْرُ الْخَلَايقِ ذُوالْبِرِّ وَ التَّقْوٰى؟ \nAYNA SADRUL KHALAAA-EQE ZUL BIRRE WAT TAQWAA \nWhere is the President of all creatures, who is both the beneficent and God fearing?\nاَيْنَ ابْنُ النَّبِىِّ الْمُصْطَفٰى؟\nAYNABNUN NABIYYENIL MUSTAFAA \nWhere is the son of the chosen (Al-Mustafa) prophet\nوَابْنُ عَلِىٍّ الْمُرْتَضٰىَ؟\nWABNO A’LIYYENIL MURTA-ZAA \nAnd the son of Ali al-Murtaza?\nوَ ابْنُ خَدِيْجَةَ الْغَرَّآءِ؟\nWABNO KHADEEJATAL GHARRAAA-E \nAnd the son of Khadijat-ul-Gharra (The Luminous)\nوَابْنُ فَاطِمَةَ الْكُبْرٰى؟\nWABNO FAATEMATAL KUBRAA \nAnd the son of Fatematul-Kubra (the Great)?\nبِاَبِىْ اَنْتَ وَ اُمِّىْ وَ نَفْسِىْ لَكَ الْوِقَآءُ وَ الْحِمٰى\nBE-ABEE ANTA WA UMMEE WA NAFSEE LAKAL WEQAAA-O WAL HEMAA \nMay my father and my mother and my self be sacrificed for your safety and protection\nيَابْنَ السَّادَةِ الْمُقَرَّبِيْنَ \nYABNAS SAADATIL MOQARRABEENA \nO son of the masters, the favourite ones. \nيَابْنَ النُّجَبَآءِ الْاَكْرِمِيْنَ \nYABNAN NOJABAAA-IL AKRAMEENA \nO son of the noble ones, the honoured ones.\nيَابْنَ الْهُدَاةِ الْمَهْدِيِّيْنَ \nYABNAL HODAATIL MAHDIYYEENA \nO son of the guides and the divinely guided ones\nيَابْنَ الْخِيَرَةِ الْمُهَذَّبِيْنَ \nYABNAL KHIYARATIL MOHAZZABEENA \nO son of the preferred refined ones.\nيَابْنَ الْغَطَارِفَةِ الْاَنْجَبِيْنَ \nYABNAL GHATAAREFATIL ANJABEENA \nO son of the Magnanimous ones of the purest descent.\nيَابْنَ الْاَطَائِبِ الْمُطَهَّرِيْنَ \nYABNAL ATAA-EBIL MOTAHHAREENA \nO son of the most righteous.\nيَابْنَ الْخَضَارِمَةِ الْمُنْتَجَبِيْنَ \nYABNAL KHAZAAREMATIL MUNTAJABEENA \nO son of the benevolent selected ones.\nيَابْنَ الْقَمَاقِمَةِ الْاَكْرَمِيْنَ \nYABNAL QAMAAQEMATIL AKRAMEENA \nO son of the generous honoured ones.\nيَابْنَ الْبُدُوْرِ الْمُنِيْرَةٍ يَابْنَ السُّرُجِ الْمُضِيْئَةِ \nYABNAL BODOORIL MONEERATE YABNAS SOROJIL MOZEEE-ATE \nO son of the luminous moons. O son of the shinning lights.\nيَابْنَ الشُّهُبِ الثَّاقِبَةِ يَابْنَ الْاَنْجُمِ الزَّاهِرَةِ \nYABNASH SHOHOBIS SAAQEBATE YABNAL ANJOMIZ ZAAHERATE \nO son of the piercing meteors. O son of the bright starts.\nيَابْنَ السُّبُلِ الْوَاضِحَةِ يَابْنَ الْاَعْلَامِ الْلَائِحَةِ \nYABNAS SOBOLIL WAAZIHATE YABNAL AA’-LAAMIL LAA-EHATE \nO son of the clear paths. O son of the clear sings.\nيَابْنَ الْعُلُوْمِ الْكَامِلَةِ يَابْنَ السُّنَنِ الْمَشْهُوْرَةِ \nYABNAL O’LOOMIL KAAMELATE YABNAS SONANIL MASH-HOORATE \nO son of the perfect knowledge. O son of the well-known examples of conduct.\nيَابْنَ الْمَعَالِمِ الْمَاْثُوْرَةِ يَابْنَ الْمُعْجِزَاتِ الْمَوْجُوْدَةِ \nYABNAL MA-A’ALEMIL MAASOORATE YABNAL MOA’-JEZAATIL MAWJOODATE \nO son of the recorded knowledges. O son of the living miracles.\nيَابْنَ الدَّلَائِلِ الْمَشْهُوْدَةِ \nYABNAL DALAAA-ELIL MASH-HOODATE \nO son of the obvious proofs.\nيَابْنَ الصِّرَاطِ الْمُسْتَقِيْمِ \nYABNAS SERAATIL MUSTAQEEME \nO son of the straight path.\nيَابْنَ النَّبَاءِ الْعَظِيْمِ \nYABNAN NABA-IL A’ZEEME \nO son of the mighty tidings. \nيَابْنَ مَنْ هُوَ فِىْ اُمِّ الْكِتَابِ لَدَى اللهِ عَلِىٌّ حَكِيْمٌ \nYABNA MAN HOWA FEE UMMIL KETAABE LADALLAAHE A’LIYYUN HAKEEMUN \nO son of the one who is pronounced the most exalted. The most wise in Ummul-kitab by Allah. \nيَابْنَ الْآيَاتِ وَ البَيِّنَاتِ \nYABNAL AAYAATE WAL BAYYENAATE \nO son of the signs and the clear proofs.\nيَابْنَ الدَّلَائِلِ الظَّاهِرَاتِ \nYABNAD DALAAA-ELIZ ZAAHERAATE \nO son of the apparent proofs.\nيَابْنَ الْبَرَاهِيْنِ الْوَاضِحَاتِ الْبَاهِرَاتِ \nYABNAL BARAAHEENIL WAAZEHAATIL BAAHERAATE \nO son of the brilliant and clear proofs.\nيَابْنَ الْحُجَجِ الْبَالِغَاتِ \nYABNAL HOJAJIL BAALEGHAATE \nO son of the conclusive evidences.\nيَابْنَ النِّعَمِ السَّابِغَاتِ \nYABNAN NE-A’MIS SAABEGHAATE \nO son of the abundant bounties.\nيَابْنَ طٰهٰ وَ الْمُحْكَمَاتِ \nYABNA TAA-HAA WAL MOHKAMAATE \nO son of Ta-ha and the clear verses.\nيَابْنَ يٰسٓ وَ الذَّارِيَاتِ \nYABNA YAA-SEEN WAZ ZAAREYAATE\nO son of Ya-Sin  (Holy Prophet and his infallible progeny) and Zariyat  (the Scatterers)\nيَابْنَ الطُّوْرِ وَ الْعَادِيَاتِ \nYABNAT TOORE WAL A’ADEYAATE \nO son of the Tur (mount) and Aadiyat (the charger).\nيَابْنَ مَنْ دَنٰى فَتَدَلّٰى فَكَانَ قَابَ قَوْسَيْنِ اَوْ اَدْنٰى \nYABNA MAN DANAA FATADALLAA FAKAANA QAABA QAWSAYNE AW ADNAA \nO son of the one who drew near, ten he suspended, so he was the measure of two bows or closer still.\nدُنُوًّا وَ اقْتِرَابًا مِّنَ الْعَلِىِّ الْاَعْلٰى \nDONUWWAN WAQTERAABAN MENAL A’LIYYIL AA’-LAA \nThis is the nearest position to the All-High.\nلَيْتَ شِعْرِىْ اَيْنَ اسْتَقَرَّتْ بِكَ النَّوٰى \nLAYTA SHEA’REE AYNAS TAQARRAT BEKAN NAWAA\nWould that I know where your state of being far is settled.\nبَلْ اَىُّ اَرْضٍ تُقِلُّكَ اَوْ ثَرٰى \nBAL AYYO ARZIN TOQILLOKA AW SARAA \nOr which, earth of soil has embraced you;\nاَبِرَضْوٰى اَوْ غَيْرِهَا اَمْ ذِىْ طُوٰى؟\nA-BE RAZWAA AW GHAYREHAA AM ZEE TOWAA \nIs it in the mountain of Razwa or the other (mountain) or in Zee-Towaa?\nعَزِيْزٌ عَلَىَّ اَنْ اَرَى الْخَلْقَ وَ لَا تُرٰي \nA’ZEEZUN A’LAYYA AN ARAL KHALQA WA LAA TORAA\nIt is intolerable for me that I see the people but do not see you.\nوَ لَا اَسْمَعُ لَكَ حَسِيْسًا وَّ لَا نَجْوٰى \nWA LAA ASMA-O’ LAKA HASEESAN WA LAA NAJWAA\nAnd, neither do I hear a sigh of breath nor (any) whispering from you.\nعَزِيْزٌ عَلَىَّ اَنْ تُحِيْطَ بِكَ دُوْنَىِ الْبَلْوٰى \nA’ZEEZUN A’LAYYA AN TOHEETA BEKA DOONAYIL BALWAA \nIt is intolerable for me that you are surrounded by calamities \nوَلَا يَنَالُكَ مِنِّىْ ضَجِيْجٌ وَلَا شَكْوٰى \nWA LAA YANAALOKA MINNEE ZAJEEJUN WA LAA SHAKWAA \nand that neither my plaintive cry nor my complaint reaches you.\nبِنَفْسِىْ اَنْتَ مِنْ مُّغَيَّبٍ لَمْ يَخْلُ مِنَّا \nBE-NAFSEE ANTA MIN MOGHAYYABIN LAM YAKH-LO MINNAA\nMay (I) myself by sacrificed for you who seems to be concealed (physically), but not away from us.\nبِنَفْسِىْ اَنْتَ مِنْ نَازِحٍ مَا نَزَحَ عَنَّا \nBE-NAFSEE ANTA MIN NAAZEHIN MAA NAZAHA A’NNAA\nMay (I) myself be sacrificed for you who seems to be emigrant (but) not far from us.\nبِنَفْسِىْ اَنْتَ اُمْنِيَّةُ شَآئِقٍ يَتَمَنّٰى مِنْ مُؤْمِنٍ وَ مُؤْمِنَةٍ ذَكَرٰى فَحَنَّا \nBE-NAFSEE ANTA UMNIYYATO SHAA-EQIN YATAMANNAA MIN MOMININ WA MOMINATIN ZIKARAA FA-HANNAA\nMay (I) myself be sacrificed for you who is the goal or aspirations of every faithful man and woman who desires you, remembers you and moans for you.\nبِنَفْسِىْ اَنْتَ مِنْ عَقِيْدِ عِزٍّ لَا يُسَامٰى \nBE-NAFSEE ANTA MIN A’QEEDE IZZIN LAA YOSAAMAA\nMay (I) myself be sacrificed for you who is bound to lofty honour which can never be reached (by anyone).\nبِنَفْسِىْ اَنْتَ مِنْ اَثِيْلِ مَجْدٍ لَا يُجَارٰى \nBE-NAFSEE ANTA MIN ASEELE MAJDIN LAA YOJAARAA\nMay (I) myself be sacrificed for you whose original eminence cannot be equalled.\nبِنَفْسِىْ اَنْتَ مِنْ تِلَادِ نِعَمٍ لَا تُضَاهٰى \nBE-NAFSEE ANTA MIN TELAADE NE-A’MIN LAA TOZAAHAA \nMay (I) myself by sacrificed for you who is the ancestral bounty which cannot be resembled.\nبِنَفْسِىْ اَنْتَ مِنْ نَصِيْفِ شَرَفٍ لَا يُسَاوٰى \nBE-NAFSEE ANTA MIN NASEEFE SHARAFIN LAA YOSAAWAA \nMay (I) myself be sacrificed for you, the partaker of nobility, the like of which is not possible.\nاِلٰى مَتٰى اَحَارُ فِيْكَ يَا مَوْلَايَ؟\nELAA MATAA A-HAARO FEEKA YAA MAWLAAYA \nHow long am I to bewail for you, O my Master!\nوَ اِلٰى مَتٰى وَ اَىُّ خِطَآبٍ اَصِفُ فِيْكَ وَ اَىُّ نَجْوٰى؟\nWA ELAA MATAA WA AYYA KHETAABIN ASEFO FEEKA WA AYYA NAJWAA \nAnd how long and with which word should I praise you, and what secret talk (should I adopt with you).\nعَزِيْزٌ عَلَىَّ اَنْ اُجَابَ دُوْنَكَ وَ اُنَاغٰى \nA’ZEEZUN A’LAYYA AN OJAABA DOONAKA WA ONAAGHAA \nIt is intolerable for me to talk and receive a reply from persons than you.\nعَزِيْزٌ عَلَىَّ اَنْ اَبْكِيَكَ وَ يَخْذُلَكَ الْوَرٰى \nAZEEZUN A’LAYYA AN ABKEYAKA WA YAKHZOLAKAL WARAA\nIt is intolerable for me that I cry for you while all others forsake you.\nعَزِيْزٌ عَلَىَّ اَنْ يَجْرِىَ عَلَيْكَ دُوْنَهُمْ مَا جَرٰى \nAZEEZUN A’LAYYA AN YAJREYA A’LAYKA DOONAHUM MAA JARAA \nIt is intolerable for me that this (isolation) befalls you instead of befalling others.\nهَلْ مِنْ مُعِيْنٍ فَاُطِيْلَ مَعَهُ الْعَوَيْلَ وَ الْبُكَاءَ؟\nHAL MIN MO-E’ENIN FA-OTEELA MA-A’HUL A’WEELA WAL BOKAAA-A\nIs there any helper with whom I may prolong my lamentation and weeping.\nهَلْ مِنْ جَزُوْعٍ فَاُسَاعِدَ جَزَعَهٗ اِذَا خَلَا؟\nHAL MIN JAZOO-I’N A-OSAA-E’DA JAZA-A’HU EZAA KHALAA\nIs there any mourner with whom I may join when he mourns alone.\nهَلْ قَذِيَتْ عَيْنٌ فَسَاعَدَتْهَا عَيْنِىْ عَلَى الْقَذٰى؟\nHAL QAZEYAT A’YNUN FASAA-A’DAT-HAA A’YNEE A’LAL QAZAA \nIs there any eye weeping of a thorn, that my eye may sympathise with it.\nهَلْ اِلَيْكَ يَابْنَ اَحْمَدَ سَبِيْلٌ فَتُلْقٰى؟\nHAL ELAYKA YABNA AHMADA SABEELUN FATULQAA \nO the son of Ahmad! Is there a way through which you may be met.\nهَلْ يَتَّصِلُ يَوْمُنَا مِنْكَ بِعِدَةِ فَنَحْظٰى؟ \nHAL YATTASELO YAWMONAA MINKA BE-E’DATIN FA-NAHZAA\nMay our day (of separation) join the day of reappearance by which we enjoy?\nمَتٰى نَرِدُ مَنَاهِلَكَ الرَّوِيَّةَ فَنَرْوٰى؟\nMATAA NAREDO MANAAHELAKAR RAWIYYATA FA-NARWAA \nWhen shall we arrive at your streams for drink, with which to quench our thirst for you?\nمَتٰى نَنْتَقِعُ مِنْ عَذْبِ مَآئِكَ فَقَدْ طَالَ الصَّدٰى؟\nMATAA NANTAQE-O’ MIN A’ZBE MAAA-EKA FAQAD TAALAS SADAA\nWhen shall we get benefit of your sweet water, for already the thirst has lasted too long?\nمَتٰى نُغَادِيْكَ وَ نُرَاوِحُكَ فَنُقِرُّ عَيْنًا؟\nMATAA NOGHAADEEKA WA NORAA-WEHOKA FA-NOQIRRO A’YNAN\nWhen shall we spend morning and evening with you to delight our eyes with a glance (at you)?\nمَتٰى تَرَانَا وَ نَرَاكَ وَ قَدْ نَشَرْتَ لِوَآءَ النَّصْرِ تُرٰى؟\nMATAA TARAANAA WA NARAAKA WA QAD NASHARTA LEWAAA-AN NASRE TORAA \nWhen shall you see us and we shall see you; then you shall be seen unfurling the flag of victor.\nاَتَرَانَا نَحُفُّ بِكَ وَ اَنْتَ تَاُمُّ الْمَلَاَ وَ قَدْ مَلَاْتَ الْاَرْضَ عَدْلًا \nA-TARAANAA NAHUFFO BEKA WA ANTA TA-UMMUL MALA-AWA QAD MALAA-TAL ARZA A’DLAN \nWill you see us gathered around you and you are leading all the people. Then already you have filled the earth with justice \nوَ اَذَقْتَ اَعْدَآئَكَ هَوَانًا وَ عِقَابًا\nWA AZAQTA AA’-DAAA-EKA HAWAANAN WA E’QAABAN\nand have made your enemies taste the disgrace (of defeat) and retribution.\nوَ اَبَرْتَ الْعُتَاةَ وَ جَحَدَةِ الْحَقِّ وَ قَطَعْتَ دَابِرَ الْمُتَكَبِّرِيْنَ \nWA ABARTAL O’TAATA WA JAHADATAL HAQQE WA QATA’-TA DAABERAL MOTAKABBEREENA\nAnd you have destroyed rebels and deniers of the truth. And you have annihilated the last remains of the arrogant \nوَ اجْتَثَثْتَ اُصُوْلَ الظَّالِمِيْنَ \nWAJ TASASTA OSOOLAZ ZAALEMEENA\nand uprooted the foundation of the unjust people.\nوَ نَحْنُ نَقُوْلُ ’اَلْحَمْدُ ِللهِ رَبِّ الْعَالَمِيْنَ‘\nWA NAHNO NAQOOLO ‘AL-HAMDO LILLAAHE RABBIL A’ALAMEENA;\nThen we say: Praise be to Allah, Lord of the Worlds.\nاَللّٰهُمَّ اَنْتَ كَشَّافُ كُرَبِ وَ الْبَلْوٰى \nALLAAHUMMA ANTA KASHSHAAFUL KURBI WAL BALWAA\nO Allah You are the Remover of agonies and calamities.\nوَ اِلَيْكَ اَسْتَعْدِىْ فَعِنْدَكَ الْعَدْوٰى \nWA ELAYKA ASTA’-DEE FA-I’NDAKAL A’DWAA\nAnd You are the one from whom I seek help; then with you is the sanctuary.\nوَ اَنْتَ رَبُّ الْاٰخِرَةِ وَ الدُّنْيَا \nWA ANTA RABBUL AAKHERATE WAD DUNYAA\nAnd You are Lord of the Hereafter and this World;\nفَاَغِثْ يَا غِيَاثَ الْمُسْتَغِيْثِيْنَ عُبَيْدَكَ الْمُبْتَلٰى \nFA-AGHIS YAA GHEYAASAL MUSTAGHEESEENA O’BAYDAKAL MUBTALAA\nSo help O helper of those who seek help, your poor afflicted servant.\nوَ اَرِهٖ سَيِّدَهٗ يَا شَدِيْدَ الْقُوٰى \nWA AREHI SAYYEDAHU YAA SHADEEDAL QOWAA\nAnd show him his Master; O Severer of strength\nوَاَزِلْ عَنْهُ بِهِ الْاَسٰى وَ الْجَوٰى \nWA AZIL A’NHO BEHIL ASAA WAL JAWAA\nAnd through him (Imam a.s.) remove his (Your servant’s) grief and sorrow.\nوَ بَرِّدْ غَلِيْلَهٗ يَا مَنْ عَلَى الْعَرْشِ اسْتَوٰى \nWA BARRID GHALEELAHU YAA MAN A’LAL A’RSHIS-TAWAA \nAnd cool the burning of his hurt, O You who is firm in the Heavenly throne of power \nوَ مَنْ اِلَيْهِ الرُّجْعٰى وَالْمُنْتَهٰى \nWA MAN ELAYHIR RUJ-A’A WAL MUNTAHAA\nand towards Whom is the return and ultimate end.\nاَللّٰهُمَّ وَ نَحْنُ عَبِيْدُكَ التَّائِقُوْنَ اِلٰى وَلِيِّكَ الْمُذَكِّرِ بِكَ وَ بِنَبِيِّكَ \nALLAAHUMMA WA NAHNO A’BEEDOKAT TAAA-EQOONA ELAA WALIYYEKAL MOZAKKERE BEKA WA BE-NABIYYEKA \nO Allah! We are Your enamoured servants of Your appointed regent who reminds us of You and Your Prophet (s.a.w.a.).\nخَلَقْتَهٗ لَنَا عِصْمَةً وَّ مَلَاذًا وَ اَقَمْتَهٗ لَنَا قِوَامًا وَ مَعَاذًا \nKHALAQTAHU LANAA I’SMATAN WA MALAAZAA WA AQAMTAHOO LANAA QEWAAMAN WA MA-A’AZAN\nHe whom You created for us as our saviour and defender, and set him for us as a protector and refuge.\nوَ جَعَلْتَهٗ لِلْمُؤْمِنِيْنَ مِنَّا اِمَامًا \nWA JA-A’LTAHU LIL MOMINEENA MINNAA EMAAMAN\nAnd appoint him a leader (Imam) for the true believers amongst us.\nفَبَلِّغْهُ مِنَّا تَحِيَّةً وَّ سَلَامًا \nFA-BALLIGHHO MINNAA TAHIYYATAN WA SALAAMAN\nSo convey to him our greetings and salutations.\nوَ زِدْنًا بِذٰلِكَ يَا رَبِّ اِكْرَامًا \nWA ZIDNAA BE ZAALEKA YAA RABBE IKRAAMAN\nAnd increase honour because of this (greeting) O Lord.\nوَاجْعَلْ مُسْتَقَرَّهٗ لَنَا مُسْتَقَرًّا وَ مُقَامًا \nWAJ-A’L MUSTAQARRAHU LANAA MUSTAQARRAN WA MOQAAMAN\nAnd make his abode (in paradise) also a home and lasting place for us.\nوَ اَتْمِمْ نِعْمَتَكَ بِتَقْدِيْمِكَ اِيَّاهُ اَمَامَنَا \nWA ATMIM NEA’-MATAKA BE-TAQDEEMEKA IYYAAHO AMAAMANAA \nAnd complete Your favours by appointing him as our guide. \nحَتّٰى تُوْرِدَنَا جِنَانَكَ وَ مُرَافَقَةِ الشُّهَدَآءِ مِنْ خُلَصَآئِكَ \nHATTAA TOOREDANAA JENAANAKA WA MORAAFAQATASH SHO-HADAAA-E MIN KHOLASAAA-EKA\nTill you make us enter Your Paradise; and (bestow on us) the companionship of the martyrs from amongst those of our adorers.\nاَللّٰهُمَّ صَلِّ عَلٰى مُحَمَّدٍ وَّ اٰلِ مُحَمَّدٍ \nALLAAHUMMA SALLE A’LAA MOHAMMADIN WA AALE MOHAMMADIN \nO Allah! Bestow your blessings upon Mohammad and the progeny of Mohammad.\nوَصَلِّ عَلٰى مَحَمَّدٍ جَدِّهِ وَ رَسُوْلِكَ السَّيِّدِ الْاَكْبَرِ \nWA SALLE A’LAA MOHAMMADIN JADDEHI WA RASOOLEKAS SAYYEDIL AKBARE \nAnd bless his grandfather Mohammad and Your Messenger the elder Master.\nوَعَلٰى اَبِيْهِ السَّيِّدِ الْاَصْغَرِ \nWA A’LAA ABEEHIS SAYYEDIL ASGHARE\nAnd upon his father (Ali) the younger Master.\nوَ جَدَّتِهِ الصِّدِّيْقَةِ الْكُبْرٰى فَاطِمِةَ بِنْتِ مَحَمَّدٍ \nWA JADDATEHIS SIDDEEQATIL KUBRAA FAATEMATA BINTE MOHAMMADIN\nAnd his grandmother, the great truthful daughter of Mohammad (s.a.w.a.)\nوَ عَلٰى مَنِ اصْطَفَيْتَ مِنْ اٰبَآئِهِ الْبَرَرَةِ \nWA A’LAA MANIS TAFAYTA MIN AABAAA-EHIL BARARATE\nAnd upon whom you have selected from among his virtuous ancestors.\nوَ عَلَيْهِ اَفْضَلَ وَ اَكْمَلَ وَ اَتَمَّ وَ اَدْوَمَ وَ اَكْثَرَ وَ اَوْفَرَ \nWA A’LAYHE AFZALA WA AKMALA WA ATAMMA WA ADWAMA WA AKSARA WA AWFARA \nAnd on him (Imam a.s.) (bestow) the best, the plentiful, the most perfect, the everlasting, the most and the numerous (blessings)\nمَا صَلَّيْتَ عَلٰى اَحَدٍ مِّنْ اَصْفِيَآئِكَ وَ خِيَرَتِكَ مِنْ خَلْقِكَ \nMAA SALLAYTA A’LAA AHADIN MIN ASFEYAAA-EKA WA KHEYARATEKA MIN KHALQEKA\n (as) whatever you bestowed on any of Your virtuous and chosen ones from among our creatures.\nوَ صَلِّ عَلَيْهِ صَلوٰةً لَا غَايَةَ لِعَدَدِهَا \nWA SALLE A’LAYHE SALAATAN LAA GHAAYATA LE-A’DADEHAA \nAnd favour him with endless count of blessings\nوَلَا نِهَايَةَ لِمَدَدِهَا وَ لَا نَفَادَ لِاَمَدِهَا \nWA LAA NEHAAYATA LE-MADADEHAA WA LAA NAFAADA LE-AMADEHAA\nwhich never gets end nor limitation.\nاَللّٰهُمَّ وَ اَقِمْ بِهِ الْحَقَّ \nALLAAHUMMA WA AQIM BEHIL HAQQA\nO Allah! And through him set up the truth\nوَ اَدْحِضْ بِهِ الْبَاطِلَ وَ اَدِلْ بِهٖ اَوْلِيَآئَكَ \nWA ADHIZ BEHIL BAATELA WA ADIL BEHI AWLEYAAA-AKA\nAnd make the falsehood vanished through him. And prepare the victory of Your friends,\nوَ اَذْلِلْ بِهٖ اَعْدَآئَكَ \nWA AZLIL BEHI AA’-DAAA-AKA\nAnd disgrace Your enemies through him.\nوَ صِلِ اللّٰهُمَّ بَيْنَنَا وَ بَيْنَهٗ وُصْلَةً تُؤَدِّىْ اِلٰى مُرَافَقَتِ سَلَفِهٖ \nWA SELIL LAAHUMMA BAYNANAA WA BAYNAHU WUSLATAN TO-ADDEE ELAA MORAAFAQATE SALAFEHI\nO Allah, set a relationship between us and him that grants us the honour of the company of his ancestors.\nوَاجْعَلْنَا مِمَّنْ يَاْخُذُ بِحُجْزَتِهِمْ وَ يَمْكُثُ فِىْ ظِلِّهِمْ \nWAJ-A’LNAA MIMMAN YAA-KHOZO BE-HUJZATEHIM WA YAMKOSO FEE ZILLEHIM \nAnd let us be of those who seek their company and reside in their shelter.\nوَ اَعِنَّا عَلٰى تَاْدِيَةِ حُقُوْقِهٖ اِلَيْهِ وَالْاِجْتِهَادِ فِىْ طَاعَتِهٖ \nWA A-I’NNAA A’LAA TAA-DEYATE HOQOOQEHI ELAYHE WAL IJTEHAADE FEE TAA-A’TEHI \nAnd help us in fulfilling our dues to him and in striving hard to his obedience \nوَاجْتِنَابِ مَعْصِيَتِهٖ \nWAJ TENAABE MA’-SEYATEHI\nand to avoid disobeying him.\nوَامْنُنْ عَلَيْنَا بِرِضَاهُ وَ هَبْ لَنَا رَاْفَتَهٗ وَ رَحْمَتَهٗ وَ دُعَآئَهٗ وَ خَيْرَهٗ \nWAM-NUN A’LAYNAA BE-REZAAHO WA HAB LANAA RAA-FATAHU WA RAHMATAHU WA DO-A’AA-AHU WA KHAYRAHU\nAnd grant us his pleasure and bestow on us his affection and his compassion and his supplication and his goodness\nمَا نَنَالُ بِهٖ سَعَةً مِّنْ رَحْمَتِكَ وَ فَوْزًا عِنْدَكَ \nMAA NANAALO BEHI SA-A’TAN MIN RAHMATEKA WA FAWZAN I’NDAKA\nWhereby through him we may receive the vastness of Your Mercy and Success with You\nوَاجْعَلْ صَلٰوتَنَا بِهٖ مَقْبُوْلَةً \nWAJ-A’L SALAATANAA BEHI MAQBOOLATAN\nAnd for his sake let our prayers be accepted\nوَ ذُنُوْبَنَا بِهٖ مَغْفُوْرَۃً\nWA ZONOOBANAA BEHI MAGHFOORATAN\nAnd for his sake let our sins be forgiven\nوَ دُعَآئَنَا بِهٖ مُسْتَجَابًا \nWA DO-A’AA-ANAA BEHI MUSTAJAABAN\nAnd for his sake let our requests be granted\nوَاجْعَلْ اَرْزَاقَنَا بِهٖ مَبْسُوْطَةً \nWAJ-A’L ARZAAQANAA BEHI MABSOOTATAN\nAnd for his sake let our sustenance be abundant\nوَ هُمُوْمَنَا بِهٖ مَكْفِيَّةً \nWA HOMOOMANAA BEHI MAKFIYYATAN\nAnd for his sake let our sadness be relieved\nوَ حَوَآئِجَنَا بِهٖ مَقْضِيَّةً \nWA HAWAAA-EJANAA BEHI MAQZIYYATAN\nAnd for his sake let our wants be granted\nوَ اَقْبِلْ اِلَيْنَا بِوَجْهِكَ الْكَرِيْمِ \nWA AQBIL ELAYNAA BE-WAJHEKAL KAREEME\nAnd Your turn to us through Your Honoured face\nوَاقْبَلْ تَقَرُّبَنَا اِلَيْكَ \nWAQ-BAL TAQARROBANAA ELAYKA\nAnd accept our proximity with you.\nوَانْظُرْ اِلَيْنَا نَظْرَةً رَحِيْمَةً \nWAN-ZUR ELAYNAA NAZRATAN RAHEEMATAN \nAnd cast upon us Your merciful look, \nنَسْتَكْمِلُ بِهَا الْكَرَامَةِ عِنْدَكَ \nNASTAKMELO BEHAL KARAAMATA I’NDAKA\nthrough which our achievement of honour from you may be perfected;\nثُمَّ لَا تَصْرِفْهَا عَنَّا بِجُوْدِكَ \nSUMMA LAA TASRIF-HAA A’NNAA BE-JOODEKA\nThen never deprive us of it by Your generosity.\nوَاسْقِنَا مِنْ حَوْضِ جَدِّهِ صَلَّى اللهُ عَلَيْهِ وَ آلِهٖ \nWAS-QENAA MIN HAWZE JADDEHI SALLAL LAAHO A’LAYHE WA AALEHI \nAnd quench our thirst from the cistern of his (Imam a.s.) grandfather, may Allah bless him and his progeny, \nبِكَاْسِهٖ وَ بِيَدِهٖ رَيًّا رَوِيًّا هَنِيْٓئًا سَآئِغًا \nBEKAA-SEHI WA BE-YADEHI RAYYAN RAWIYYAN HANEE-AN SAAA-EGHAN \nin his own cup and from his own hand. A sweet, cool, clear, agreeable drink \nلَا ظَمَأَ بَعْدَهٗ يَا اَرْحَمَ الرَّاحِمِيْنَ\nLAA ZAMA-A BA’-DAHU YAA ARHAMAR RAAHEMEENA\nafter which no thirst is felt. O Most Merciful of All.", 
    "title": "Dua e Nudbah"
}